on the basis of copious preclinical data supporting the preventive efficacy of small fruits such as berries and grapes chen and colleagues conducted a randomized noncomparative phase ii trial evaluating two doses of strawberry powder 60 gd or 30 gd for six months to prevent esophageal cancer in china reported in this issue of the journal beginning on page 41 60 gd reduced the histologic grade of dysplastic lesions and reduced localized biomarkers whereas 30 gd was not effectivefundamental questions remain such as the best formulation of strawberry powder the active components associated with powder and the actual mechanism of action and standardized preparations will be required to permit the widespread use of strawberry powder with a predicable outcomeclearly however this work is a good example of proofofprinciple and highlights the important role of diet nutrition and natural products in cancer prevention2012 aacr